For many years the Tempo Run has been
considered as a linchpin around which a

00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:11.909
lot of

00:00:11.909 --> 00:00:17.149
top athletes training is done. And Tempo
running is often ill-defined as well

00:00:17.149 --> 00:00:21.529
and misunderstood because of the
different grasp of what Tempo Running

00:00:21.529 --> 00:00:22.490
really is.

00:00:22.490 --> 00:00:26.300
Tempo running is often associated with
about 2.5 millimoles of

00:00:26.300 --> 00:00:27.449
Lactate

00:00:27.449 --> 00:00:31.789
but most people don't have access
to lactate measurement and so you have

00:00:31.789 --> 00:00:34.450
to base it on velocity or on heart rate.

00:00:34.450 --> 00:00:38.760
And that two paces that that's most associated with

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:40.829
are your marathon pace,

00:00:40.829 --> 00:00:42.900
and your heart marathon pace.

00:00:42.900 --> 00:00:47.240
Tempo running for shorter distances
like for 10k race like doing a

00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:52.360
three mile run for a 6 mile race that
might be too much add to higher

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:55.250
intensity and then interval training is
a better idea.

